-- Scotiabank’s Dynamic Funds Hires Zyblock as Chief Strategist
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-05-15T16:00:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-15/scotiabank-s-dynamic-funds-hires-zyblock-as-chief-strategist.html
Dynamic Funds, a unit of  Bank of Nova
Scotia , hired Myles Zyblock for chief investment strategist as
the fund manager reorganizes.  Zyblock, previously chief institutional strategist for
 Royal Bank of Canada (RY) ’s investment-banking unit, takes over from
Rohit Sehgal, Dynamic Funds said today in a statement. Sehgal is
moving from mutual funds to managing alternative assets, the
Toronto-based firm said.  Dynamic Funds also appointed Alexander Lane as co-portfolio
manager for the Dynamic Power Canadian Growth Fund and Dynamic
Power Balance Fund, the company said.  In September, fund manager Chuk Wong will assume lead
portfolio management responsibilities for Dynamic  Emerging
Markets  Class, which he has co-managed with Sehgal since
inception, the firm said. Yassen Dimitrov takes over as lead
portfolio manager for Dynamic Financial Services Fund, which he
co-managed with Sehgal since July 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
